text: The Baltimore oriole (Icterus galbula) is a small icterid blackbird. It is common in eastern North America as a migratory breeding bird. The Baltimore oriole is the state bird of Maryland. It is also the inspiration for the Baltimore Orioles baseball team. ==References== Category:Icteridae Category:Maryland Category:Birds of North America Category:Birds of Central America Category:Birds of South America
